  "page": {
    "documentTitle": "假兩難 | Concept Reading Lab",
    "bodyClass": "knowledge-page knowledge-false-dilemma",
    "heroHtml": "<div class=\"hero-inner\">\n  <div>\n    <p class=\"kicker\">Knowledge Study / logic / options / compression</p>\n    <h1>假兩難</h1>\n    <p class=\"topic-subtitle\">False Dilemma</p>\n    <p class=\"thesis\">當問題被壓縮成『不是 A 就是 B』時，討論常會突然變簡單，但也可能把真正可行的第三條路、漸進方案或條件式答案一起消失。</p>\n    <div class=\"hero-prompt\">\n      <strong>Read For</strong>\n      <p>這一頁要把『這題就是二選一』和『其實是被說成只剩二選一』拆開，因為很多僵局是選項被提前砍掉的結果。</p>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n  <aside class=\"hero-note\" aria-label=\"主題資訊\">\n    <dl class=\"lexical-meta lexical-meta--knowledge\" aria-label=\"主題摘要\">\n      <div>\n        <dt>主題類型</dt>\n        <dd>推理偏誤 / 選項壓縮</dd>\n      </div>\n      <div>\n        <dt>核心問題</dt>\n        <dd>Presenting a situation as if only two options exist when more are available</dd>\n      </div>\n      <div>\n        <dt>主要判準</dt>\n        <dd>選項完整度、問題框架、漸進空間、語言壓縮</dd>\n      </div>\n      <div>\n        <dt>讀完產出</dt>\n        <dd>能更快看出討論何時被不必要地壓成兩極對立</dd>\n      </div>\n    </dl>\n    <div class=\"knowledge-map\" aria-label=\"閱讀結構示意\">\n      <span>二選一</span>\n      <span>壓縮</span>\n      <span>漏失</span>\n    </div>\n  </aside>\n</div>",
    "mainHtml": "<aside class=\"compass\" aria-label=\"頁內導覽\">\n  <span>Reading Path</span>\n  <a href=\"#core\">讀法總覽</a>\n  <a href=\"#setup\">問題設定</a>\n  <a href=\"#lenses\">判準透鏡</a>\n  <a href=\"#psychology\">心理連結</a>\n  <a href=\"#applications\">現實映射</a>\n  <a href=\"#misreadings\">誤讀校正</a>\n  <a href=\"#questions\">延伸提問</a>\n  <a href=\"#sources\">來源</a>\n</aside>\n\n<article class=\"article\">\n  <section class=\"chapter\" id=\"core\">\n    <div class=\"section-heading\">\n      <p class=\"section-label\">Orientation</p>\n      <h2>把複雜問題壓成二選一，常會同時帶來清楚感與盲點</h2>\n      <p class=\"section-lede\">假兩難之所以有吸引力，是因為它讓決策像考選擇題一樣俐落；問題在於現實常不只兩格。</p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"core-card\">\n      <p class=\"section-label\">Core Tension</p>\n      <p>壓縮選項能加速表態，但若可行空間本來就更寬，二分法只會讓團隊在錯框架裡互撞。</p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"principle-strip\" aria-label=\"本頁讀法\">\n      <div>\n        <span>01</span>\n        <strong>先問還有沒有第三類</strong>\n        <p>很多題目其實有混合、階段式或條件式答案。</p>\n      </div>\n      <div>\n        <span>02</span>\n        <strong>再分清描述與壓縮</strong>\n        <p>有時說成兩邊只是為了簡化溝通，不代表現實只有兩邊。</p>\n      </div>\n      <div>\n        <span>03</span>\n        <strong>最後把漏掉的代價算進來</strong>\n        <p>若二分法讓重要選項失語，決策品質就會被一起壓扁。</p>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n\n  <section class=\"chapter\" id=\"setup\">\n    <div class=\"section-heading\">\n      <p class=\"section-label\">Setup</p>\n      <h2>從一句『不是現在上就是永遠不上』開始</h2>\n      <p class=\"section-lede\">假兩難在策略討論、管理溝通與輿論辯論中特別常見。</p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"definition-grid\">\n      <div class=\"tile\">\n        <strong>最小劇情</strong>\n        <p>有人把架構決策說成『要嘛全面重寫，要嘛什麼都別碰』，於是分段改造、局部抽離與試點路線全被擠掉。</p>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"tile\">\n        <strong>真正難點</strong>\n        <p>一旦大家接受這個二分框架，後面就算再聰明也只能在被切窄的地板上跑。</p>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"concept-flow\" aria-label=\"問題展開\">\n      <div class=\"flow-step\">複雜問題被壓成兩端</div>\n      <div class=\"flow-arrow\">→</div>\n      <div class=\"flow-step\">其他選項失語</div>\n      <div class=\"flow-arrow\">→</div>\n      <div class=\"flow-step\">討論在假二選一中升溫</div>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"paradox-frame\">\n      <strong>Key Point</strong>\n      <p>假兩難最需要防的是：在表態變容易時，思考空間也被一起關掉。</p>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n\n  <section class=\"chapter\" id=\"lenses\">\n    <div class=\"section-heading\">\n      <p class=\"section-label\">Lenses</p>\n      <h2>四個看選項壓縮的角度</h2>\n      <p class=\"section-lede\">不是所有二分都錯，但當二分讓關鍵中間地帶消失時，就值得停下來重畫地圖。</p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"lens-grid\">\n      <article class=\"lens-card\">\n        <strong>遺漏選項</strong>\n        <p>是否存在漸進方案、試點方案或不同維度的解法？</p>\n      </article>\n      <article class=\"lens-card\">\n        <strong>維度混疊</strong>\n        <p>是不是把本可分開處理的問題硬綁成同一條軸？</p>\n      </article>\n      <article class=\"lens-card\">\n        <strong>話術速度</strong>\n        <p>二分法是否主要用來迫使快速站隊？</p>\n      </article>\n      <article class=\"lens-card\">\n        <strong>成本對照</strong>\n        <p>被排除的選項，其實是否才最符合當下資源與風險條件？</p>\n      </article>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"table-wrap\">\n      <table>\n        <thead>\n          <tr>\n            <th>二分說法</th>\n            <th>漏掉什麼</th>\n            <th>可能後果</th>\n          </tr>\n        </thead>\n        <tbody>\n          <tr>\n            <td>全上或全不上</td>\n            <td>試點、分階段導入</td>\n            <td>把可逆路徑一起關掉</td>\n          </tr>\n          <tr>\n            <td>快或穩只能選一個</td>\n            <td>重排範圍、切分風險</td>\n            <td>把治理問題誤寫成天生對立</td>\n          </tr>\n          <tr>\n            <td>支持或反對</td>\n            <td>條件支持、局部支持</td>\n            <td>對話更極化</td>\n          </tr>\n        </tbody>\n      </table>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n\n  <section class=\"chapter\" id=\"psychology\">\n    <div class=\"section-heading\">\n      <p class=\"section-label\">Psychology</p>\n      <h2>為什麼二分法這麼誘人</h2>\n      <p class=\"section-lede\">因為它能快速降低複雜度，讓人立刻知道自己站哪裡。</p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"example-grid\">\n      <div class=\"example\">\n        <strong>站隊比建模快</strong>\n        <p>二選一比把空間攤開來看省很多認知成本。</p>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"example\">\n        <strong>衝突敘事更有張力</strong>\n        <p>兩端對立比多元中間地帶更容易引發情緒與動員。</p>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"example\">\n        <strong>模糊中間比較難說</strong>\n        <p>很多中間方案需要更多條件說明，因此常在口語場域吃虧。</p>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n    <p class=\"micro-note\">假兩難不是說不能在最後二選一，而是說別太早把世界壓成只剩兩格。</p>\n  </section>\n\n  <section class=\"chapter\" id=\"applications\">\n    <div class=\"section-heading\">\n      <p class=\"section-label\">Applications</p>\n      <h2>把選項空間重新打開帶回決策</h2>\n      <p class=\"section-lede\">對工程與產品團隊來說，假兩難最常讓可逆、漸進、混合式解法提前失語。</p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"example-grid\">\n      <div class=\"example\">\n        <strong>架構演進</strong>\n        <p>全面重寫與完全不動之間，常還有抽取邊界、局部服務化與 adapter 過渡。</p>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"example\">\n        <strong>流程治理</strong>\n        <p>快與穩不是只能二選一，很多時候可以透過分層 gate 重畫 tradeoff。</p>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"example\">\n        <strong>產品策略</strong>\n        <p>功能不是全開全關，也可以限量、灰度或條件開放。</p>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n    <ul class=\"bullet-list\">\n      <li>只要有人說『不是 A 就是 B』，就值得追問至少兩個被排除的第三選項。</li>\n      <li>先把可逆方案找出來，常能讓假兩難鬆開一大半。</li>\n    </ul>\n  </section>\n\n  <section class=\"chapter\" id=\"misreadings\">\n    <div class=\"section-heading\">\n      <p class=\"section-label\">Misreadings</p>\n      <h2>三個常見誤讀</h2>\n      <p class=\"section-lede\">假兩難不是說任何二選一都錯，而是說二選一若遮掉現實可行空間就有問題。</p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"collocation-list\" aria-label=\"常見誤讀\">\n      <article class=\"collocation-card\">\n        <div>\n          <strong>有時最後真的要二選一，所以這不重要</strong>\n          <span class=\"register-tag\">校正</span>\n        </div>\n        <p>最後也許要選，但在那之前仍不該省略其他可能。</p>\n      </article>\n      <article class=\"collocation-card\">\n        <div>\n          <strong>只在辯論術才有</strong>\n          <span class=\"register-tag\">校正</span>\n        </div>\n        <p>團隊會議、產品路線與技術決策也常出現。</p>\n      </article>\n      <article class=\"collocation-card\">\n        <div>\n          <strong>中間選項一定比較好</strong>\n          <span class=\"register-tag\">校正</span>\n        </div>\n        <p>不一定，重點是讓它們有機會被看見和比較。</p>\n      </article>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n\n  <section class=\"chapter\" id=\"questions\">\n    <div class=\"section-heading\">\n      <p class=\"section-label\">Questions</p>\n      <h2>我是在面對真二選一，還是被提早關進二選一</h2>\n      </div>\n    <div class=\"prompt-grid\">\n      <article class=\"prompt-card\">\n        <strong>如果不能選 A 或 B，還有哪些第三路徑其實存在</strong>\n        <p>這個問題常能立刻打開空間。</p>\n      </article>\n      <article class=\"prompt-card\">\n        <strong>這兩端是否其實混了不同維度，才看起來像只能站隊</strong>\n        <p>拆維度後常會出現新解。</p>\n      </article>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"template-note\">\n      <strong>延伸路線</strong>\n      <p>延伸閱讀可接 dichotomy, option generation 與 decision framing。</p>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n\n  <section class=\"chapter\" id=\"sources\">\n    <div class=\"section-heading\">\n      <p class=\"section-label\">Sources</p>\n      <h2>來源與整理方式</h2>\n      <p class=\"section-lede\">這一頁以 false dilemma 為主，再把概念帶回策略、產品與架構決策。</p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"source-grid\">\n      <article class=\"source-card\">\n        <strong>主概念</strong>\n        <p>False dilemma 條目整理了把複雜情境壓成兩個選項的典型問題。</p>\n        <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/False_dilemma\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer\">False Dilemma</a>\n      </article>\n      <article class=\"source-card\">\n        <strong>相鄰概念</strong>\n        <p>Dichotomy 的一般背景有助於理解二分法何時有用、何時誤導。</p>\n        <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dichotomy\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer\">Dichotomy</a>\n      </article>\n      <article class=\"source-card\">\n        <strong>決策背景</strong>\n        <p>Decision framing 條目可作為對照，看問題框架如何塑形選項空間。</p>\n        <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Framing_effect_(psychology)\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer\">Framing Effect</a>\n      </article>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n\n  <section class=\"chapter\">\n    <div class=\"reference-box\">\n      <div>\n        <p class=\"section-label\">Reference</p>\n        <h2>下一步</h2>\n        <p>讀完後可以回頭看一個最近的僵局，刻意列出兩個被『不是 A 就是 B』擠掉的第三選項。</p>\n      </div>\n      <a class=\"reference-link\" href=\"../knowledge-topic-template.html\">打開模板</a>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n</article>"
  }
}
